<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc4157aa3-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s7615"><num value="7615">§ 7615.</num><heading> Status of participants</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Participants in the Scholarship Program shall not by reason of their participation in such program (1) be considered to be employees of the Federal Government, or (2) be counted against any personnel ceiling affecting the Veterans Health Administration.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc4157aa4-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/100/322/tII/s216/b">Pub. L. 100–322, title II, § 216(b)</ref>, <date date="1988-05-20">May 20, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/522">102 Stat. 522</ref>, § 4315; renumbered § 7615, <ref href="/us/pl/102/40/tIV/s402/b/1">Pub. L. 102–40, title IV, § 402(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1991-05-07">May 7, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/238">105 Stat. 238</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/103/446/tXII/s1201/b/1">Pub. L. 103–446, title XII, § 1201(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1994-11-02">Nov. 2, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4682">108 Stat. 4682</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
